程序包 org.texttechnology.parliament_browser_6_4.data

接口 User

  • 所有已知实现类:
    User_Impl
    public interface User
    Represents the contract for user entities within the application. This interface is intended to define common user-related functionalities that all user types must implement. It serves as a foundation for user entity management, including but not limited to authentication, authorization, and user profile management. As the application evolves, methods for managing user attributes, roles, and permissions should be added here.

      • getUserType

        java.lang.Integer getUserType()
        Retrieves the type of the user. User types are typically represented as integers, where each integer corresponds to a specific category or role within the application (e.g., regular user, admin, moderator).
        返回:
        An Integer indicating the user's type.

      • setUserType

        参数:

      • getCanEdit

        java.lang.Integer getCanEdit()
        Gets the user's permission to edit content within the application. This is usually represented as a binary value (e.g., 0 for no permission, 1 for permission granted).
        返回:
        An Integer representing whether the user has edit permissions.

      • setCanEdit

        void setCanEdit​(java.lang.Integer canEdit)
        Sets or updates the user's permission to edit content. This method allows for enabling or disabling a user's ability to perform edit operations within the application.
        参数:
        canEdit - The new edit permission status to be set for the user, represented as an Integer.
